SIMPLE: auriferous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Auriferous
<hw>Au*rif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aurifer</ets>; <ets>aurum</ets> gold + <ets>ferre</ets> to bear:
cf. F. <ets>aurif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <def>Gold-bearing; containing
or producing gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whence many a bursting stream <qex>auriferous</qex> plays.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Auriferous pyrites</b></col>, <cd>iron pyrites (iron
disulphide), containing some gold disseminated through it.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Auriflamme</ent>⟦br⟧
